What is Streamlit, and how does it differ from other web frameworks?

Streamlit is an open-source python library that makes us easy to create web application for machine learning and data science.  
It's particularly well-suited for quickly building interactive web apps around data, machine learning models, visualizations, and other computational tasks.
Streamlit is designed to be very user-friendly, with a simple API that allows developers to create web applications using Python scripts without needing extensive web development knowled
It enables developers to create functional web apps with minimal effort.
It offers widgets and components that make it easy to build interactive charts, graphs, sliders, and other data-driven UI elements.
